		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Carroll Susco</strong></span> lives in Fairfax, Virginia, and holds an <span class="smallcaps">MFA</span> from the University of Pittsburgh. She writes that she has just completed a novel about psychics, depressives, and mushroom takers &mdash; and &ldquo;Yes, Buddy, it has structure.&rdquo; The stigma of mental illness persists in her life, as do its effects. &ldquo;Only through understanding,&rdquo; she says, &ldquo;can we heal the wounds.&rdquo;</p><a href="/contributors/carroll-ann-susco" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
